Step 1: Create Maven Project

Open Command Prompt and execute:

mvn archetype:generate -DgroupId=com.example -DartifactId=maven-example -DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart -DinteractiveMode=false

Navigate to project folder:

cd maven-example
Step 2: Update pom.xml

Open pom.xml and replace with:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0
         http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">

    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <groupId>com.example</groupId>
    <artifactId>maven-example</artifactId>
    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>

    <dependencies>

        <!-- JUnit Dependency -->
        <dependency>
            <groupId>junit</groupId>
            <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
            <version>4.12</version>
            <scope>test</scope>
        </dependency>

    </dependencies>

    <build>
        <plugins>

            <!-- Compiler Plugin -->
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>3.8.1</version>

                <configuration>
                    <source>1.8</source>
                    <target>1.8</target>
                </configuration>

            </plugin>

        </plugins>
    </build>

</project>
Step 3: Create Java Program

Open file:

src/main/java/com/example/App.java

Replace with:

package com.example;

public class App {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        System.out.println("Hello, Maven");
        System.out.println("This is the simple realworld example....");

        int a = 5;
        int b = 10;

        System.out.println("Sum of " + a + " and " + b + " is " + sum(a, b));
    }

    public static int sum(int x, int y) {
        return x + y;
    }
}
Step 4: Build Maven Project

Run:

mvn clean install
Step 5: Run Maven Application

Run:

mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="com.example.App"
Maven Output
Hello, Maven
This is the simple realworld example....
Sum of 5 and 10 is 15
Step 6: Migrate Maven Project to Gradle

Run:

gradle init

When prompted:

Found a Maven build. Generate a Gradle build from this?
Type: yes
Select build script DSL:
1: Kotlin
2: Groovy

Type: 2
Generate build using new APIs and behavior?
Type: no
Step 7: Update build.gradle

Open build.gradle and replace with:

plugins {
    id 'java'
    id 'application'
}

group = 'com.example'
version = '1.0-SNAPSHOT'

repositories {
    mavenCentral()
}

dependencies {
    testImplementation 'junit:junit:4.12'
}

application {
    mainClass = 'com.example.App'
}
Step 8: Delete Old Test File

Delete the old Maven-generated test file:

src/test/java/com/example/AppTest.java

Reason:
The generated file uses old JUnit 3 syntax which causes compilation errors in modern Gradle versions.

Step 9: Build Gradle Project

Run:

gradlew clean build
Step 10: Run Gradle Application

Run:

gradlew run
Gradle Output
Hello, Maven
This is the simple realworld example....
